OL,4,Crelated home insurance claims in 2023
OL,6,FHomeowners' storm damage claims,
OL,7,Fincluding those for high winds,
OL,8,Ftotalled #133 million, with flooding
OL,9,Fadding #286 million. A further #153
OL,10,Fmillion of weather claims came from
OL,11,Fburst pipes, most of which happened in
OL,12,Fthe first three months of 2023 at the
OL,13,Ftail end of a cold winter.
OL,15,FThe average weather-related payout for
OL,16,Fhome insurance last year was
OL,17,Fapproaching #5,000, at #4,916. This
OL,18,Fwas a jump compared with 2022, when
OL,19,Fthe figure was #3,077.
